\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Uniqueness States for Geodesic Flows on Surfaces without Focal Points
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Dong Chen, Lien-Yung Kao, Kiho Park, Matthew Smith, and Régis Varão
\end_layout

\begin_layout Date
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
today
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
In this paper, we prove that for the geometric potential or a Hölder potential
 without carrying full pressure over the singular set has a unique equilibrium
 state.
 This result generalizes, and is inspired by, Burns-Climenhaga-Fisher-Thompson's
 work 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "BCFT2017"

\end_inset

 on the uniqueness of the equilibrium states for certain potentials over
 geodesic flows on compact rank 1 manifolds.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout --Separator--

\end_layout

