\end_inset

 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $(X,{\cal F})$
\end_inset

 be a flow on a compact metric space, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\vphi:X\to\R$
\end_inset

 be a continuous potential function.
 Suppose that 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{exp}^{\perp}(\vphi)<P(\vphi)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $X\times[0,\infty)$
\end_inset

 admits a decomposition 
\begin_inset Formula $({\cal P},{\cal G},{\cal S})$
\end_inset

 with the following properties: 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
begin{itemize}[font=
\backslash
normalfont]
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

