\begin_layout Theorem
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi:T^{1}M\to\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 be continuous, If 
\begin_inset Formula $P({\rm Sing})<P(\varphi)$
\end_inset

, and for all 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta>0$
\end_inset

 the potential 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

 has the Bowen property on 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G_{T}(\eta)=\{(v,t)\colon\ \frac{1}{\tau}\int_{0}^{\tau}\lambda_{T}(f_{s}v)ds\geq\eta{\rm \ {\rm and\ }}\frac{1}{\tau}\int_{0}^{\tau}\lambda_{T}(f_{-s}f_{t}v)ds\geq\eta\ \forall\tau\in[0,t]\},
\]

\end_inset

then the geodesic flow has a unique equilibrium stat for 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

